int32_t DPU_RangeProcDSP_config ( DPU_RangeProcDSP_Handle  handle,
DPU_RangeProcDSP_Config *  pConfig 
)

Description
The function is rangeProc DPU config function. It saves buffer pointer and configurations including system resources and configures EDMA for runtime range processing.

Precondition
DPU_RangeProcDSP_init() has been called
Parameters
[in]handlerangeProc DPU handle
[in]pConfigPointer to rangeProc configuration data structure
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0

DPU_RangeProcDSP_Handle DPU_RangeProcDSP_init ( int32_t *  errCode)

Description
The function is rangeProc DPU init function. It allocates memory to store its internal data object and returns a handle if it executes successfully.

Parameters
[in]errCodePointer to errCode generates from the API
Return values
Success- valid rangeProc handle
Error- NULL

int32_t DPU_RangeProcDSP_process ( DPU_RangeProcDSP_Handle  handle,
DPU_RangeProc_OutParams *  outParams 
)

Description
The function is rangeProc DPU process function. It executes FFT operation. It can be called multiple times in a frame until all chirps are handled in the frame.

Precondition
DPU_RangeProcDSP_init() has been called
Parameters
[in]handlerangeProc DPU handle
[in]outParamsDPU output parameters
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0
